{
  "texts": [
    "By doing so, the attacker aims to manipulate the model's behavior, using visually benign images that are exactly the same as the image trojans implanted in training.",
    "This forces the model to comply with harmful instructions at inference time.",
    "Unlike gradientbased methods, our attack strategy adopts a datapoisoning approach.",
    "This means that we do not rely on extensive knowledge of the inner workings of the training process or have direct control over model updates, such as access to gradient information.",
    "Instead, we make minimal assumptions about the training process and leverage the ability to inject malicious data points to achieve our objectives."
  ]
}